name: pyrender
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pyrender" %}
{% set version = "0.1.45" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/mmatl/{{ name }}/archive/refs/tags/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cfdf0f681f7763247623c751606e7d3417e3472d5b0f32cfd0389abd207e0a4f
  patches:
    - unpin_pyopengl.patch

build:
  number: 3
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - freetype-py
    - imageio
    - networkx
    - numpy
    - pillow
    - pip
    - pyglet >=1.4.10
    - pyopengl >=3.1.0
    - python  >=3.6
    - scipy
    - six
    - trimesh
    - dataclasses
  run:
    - freetype-py
    - imageio
    - networkx
    - numpy
    - pillow
    - pyglet >=1.4.10
    - pyopengl >=3.1.0
    - python  >=3.6
    - scipy
    - six
    - trimesh
    - dataclasses

test:
  imports:
    - pyrender
    - pyrender.platforms
  commands:
    - pip check
    # Disabled due to https://github.com/mmatl/pyrender/issues/203
    - pytest -k "not (test_meshes or test_offscreen)" tests
  requires:
    - pip
    - pytest
  source_files:
    - tests
    - examples

about:
  home: https://github.com/mmatl/pyrender
  summary: Easy-to-use Python renderer for 3D visualization
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - traversaro
